<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-10-12T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-10-12T03:00:00-05:00" n="602" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d602">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5045/391: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-10-12T16:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">October 12,
                                        1926—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received October 12—9:35
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>471. My 466, October 9, 4 p.m.<note n="36" xml:id="d602fn36">Not
                                printed.</note> Following from American consul general at Canton:
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“October 11, 2 p.m. Kuomintang and strike committee issued
                                    lengthy statements yesterday declaring boycott ended but
                                    reaffirming intention to carry into effect ‘economic struggle’
                                    with renewed vigor against the British and imperialists
                                    generally throughout China. A few Chinese came on the
                                        Island<note n="37" xml:id="d602fn37">Shameen.</note> today
                                    but the general public seems very slow to resume pre-strike
                                    relations, and it is still too early to judge the situation.
                                    There were no disorders.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>